questions.query: How does your project contribute to the advancement of the Arbitrum ecosystem?
questions.explanation: Core Infrastructure

questions.query: Describe your previous work or plans related to the Arbitrum ecosystem. How does your project strengthen Arbitrum's foundational infrastructure, improve developer efficiency, or accelerate the adoption of novel applications?
questions.explanation: We have developed an optimistic bridge for the mass inflow of users and funds from Ethereum and other Layer 2s to Arbitrum. Arbitrum has now grown to become one of the most transactional networks in the Pheasant Network. Pheasant Network's fast and cost-effective infrastructure undoubtedly supports the expansion of the Arbitrum ecosystem.

questions.query: If applicable, describe how your project leverages Stylus or Arbitrum Orbit Chains. What unique capabilities or use cases does this enable?
questions.explanation: N/A

questions.query: Describe your team's expertise in your chosen focus area within the Arbitrum ecosystem. Include relevant experience, publications, or past projects.
questions.explanation:
Pheasant Network was founded by Tomo and Newki. They have been active in the crypto space since 2013 and have remained committed to Ethereum in particular. Tomo has already had one Exit (M&A) in this space and Newki has extensive Ethereum development experience. The idea for Pheasant Network originated with Newki. They met and have worked together since 2017.

In addition, we operate L2 Learn ( https://l2learn.io ), a completely free learning service dedicated to Layer 2. Users who have taken the curriculum on L2 Learn can have their SBT certificate issued on Arbitrum.

questions.query: How does your project contribute significantly to the Ethereum network's infrastructure? Please provide specific examples and metrics if available.
questions.explanation: Pheasant Network is an optimistic interoperability protocol specialized for Layer 2. By applying the optimistic rollup mechanism to the interoperability, we have achieved transactions that are faster and cheaper than any other mechanism. We have already integrated with over 10 Layer 2s. (Optimism, Base, Mode, Arbitrum, ZKsync, Linea, Scroll, Polygon zkEVM, Taiko, X Layer, Fhenix, Morph, Zircuit)

questions.query: Describe any pioneering development work in your project, particularly in enhancing privacy, interoperability, or user experience.
questions.explanation: Pheasant Network applied the optimistic rollup mechanism to interoperability, resulting in transactions that are more cost-effective and faster than other mechanisms. We also developed a mechanism to decentralize the liquidity needed for interoperability across multiple secret keys, rather than pooling it in one place. In recognition of these achievements, we are selected to receive an Ethereum Foundation grant.

questions.query: What specific problems or challenges in the Ethereum ecosystem does your project address? How does your solution improve upon existing alternatives?
questions.explanation: Layer 2 was developed to improve the scalability of Ethereum, but currently the interoperability of Layer 2 is a challenge. For example, Optimism's OP Stack and Arbitrum's Orbit are interoperable within them, but interoperability across different frameworks has not been realized. We are working on connecting all Layer 2s to smooth out the Ethereum ecosystem.

questions.query: Outline your project's roadmap and how the grant funds will be used to achieve your development goals.
questions.explanation: We have already integrated more than 10 Layer 2s and will integrate more networks in the future. The grant funds will be used for development for this purpose.

questions.query: How does your project contribute to the decentralization and security of the Ethereum network?
questions.explanation: We believe that a third party role is essential for Layer 2 interoperability. For example, a role connecting OP Stack and Arbitrum Orbit will be needed in the future as I mentioned. Other than that, if Shared Sequencer expands, I expect that we will see Layer 2 that Shared Sequencer does not support. We also need different methods of interoperability to prevent power from being concentrated in the Shared Sequencer.

questions.query: How does your project contribute to the growth of the OSS ecosystem? Please provide specific examples of how your application enhances or expands the current ecosystem.
questions.explanation:
Pheasant Network leverages intent-based bridging and an advanced cross-chain swap protocol to connect 30+ blockchain networks with speed and efficiency. By seamlessly connecting fragmented blockchain ecosystems while preserving security, we enhance interoperability and streamline cross-chain interactions.

Pheasant Network is an Intent-centric solution and is expected to expand as the Intent ecosystem develops.

questions.query: What features or use cases does your dApp/App present? How is it differentiated?
questions.explanation:
We believe that by seamlessly connecting the fragmented blockchain ecosystem and tokens, the future of Web3 can be realized without users being aware of which blockchain they are using. If a user wanted to convert different tokens on different blockchains to different tokens on different blockchains, they would previously have to use DEX and Bridge separately. However, using the cross-chain swap, this can be accomplished in a single transaction.

Pheasant Network is unique in that it is fastest and most cost-effective than any other solution because of its unique optimistic mechanism.

questions.query: What are your plans for further development, and how will the grant funds be used to achieve these goals?
questions.explanation: Pheasant Network has integrated 10+ networks in Bridge and 30+ networks in Swap. More networks will be integrated in the future, and grant funds will be used to develop them.
